				<div class="postbody">
				</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">...but as far as representing my interests? Not hardly. None of them do, really. They're far too conservative.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
In most of the free world you can also vote with your feet. If the elected governing body is too contradictive to your intrests or beliefs, you pick up up and move to some where where they are more like you.  Right now, there is a lot of variety.  Even in the US though our federal government is becoming very intrusive, cultures and lifestyles vary widely.
<br />

<br />
But with the ICJ having global authority how do you disenfranchise yourself of their decisions if those decisions are uncomfortable or even dangerous to you.
<br />

<br />
A global authority, simply by omnidominium, is a tyrrany.  It can be nothing else no matter how benevolent. What ever laws it enforces will be inescapable by any man.  Can you be certain that this authority will always going to be moral and upstanding?
<br />

<br />
What happens when the world court starts making decisions on population control or food distribution?  Don't smirk, the UN is already active in these areas.
<br />

<br />
The UN programs are passive now.  They have no authority nor liberty except as a global charity.  But that is because historicly the UN has not had coersive authority.
<br />

<br />
To give them coersive authority throws everything out of check. By the laws of human nature and the congeling force of authority those programs WILL one day be enforced by the threat of violence.  The people of the world will have no say what-so-ever in the the UN and the judges of teh ICJ make.
<br />

<br />
Now consider some of the programs of teh UN and imagine them having the ability to enforce their government with violence:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.un.org/ga/coi/" target="_blank" class="postlink">An "information office" with a charter to establish a new world economic order</a>
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.wto.org/english/news_e/news_e.htm" target="_blank" class="postlink">Imagine the US being able to force Mexico to adopt thier communications standard with a world court order</a>
<br />

<br />
Heres your own chart of the UN.  poke around look at the programs teh UN has and imagine what could happen if those authorities could use the threat of force on nations and individuals unchecked.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.un.org/aboutun/chart.html" target="_blank">http://www.un.org/aboutun/chart.html</a>
<br />

<br />
###
<br />

